24/02/2025

Flexbox Properties:

--display: flex;

--justify-content: flex-start, flex-end, space-evenly, 

--align-items: flex-start, flex-end, center, stretch

--gap-it defines the gap between the html elements
Ex: gap:20px;

--flex-direction: row, column, row-reverse, column-reverse

--Order; it specifies the order of html elements

flex-grow: it defines the expansion proportion of particular element by default it is 0

flex-shrink: it defines the collapsion? compression proportion of elements by default it is 1.

flex-basis: it defines the initial size of the element by default value is auto




Implementation:

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>flexbox</title>
    <style>
        .parent{
            width: 100px;
            height: 100vh;
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
            
            
            
        }
        .child{
            height: 200px;
            width: 200px;
            border: 10px solid wheat;
            color: wheat;
        }
        .c1{
            background-color: red;
            order:1
            /*flex-grow: 2;*/
            /*flex-shrink:2;*/
        }
        .c2{
            background-color: blue;
        }
        .c3{
            background-color: green;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="parent">
        <div class="child c1">1</div>
        <div class="child c2">2</div>
        <div class="child c3">3</div>

    </div>
</body>
</html>
